translated: Carl Theodor Johannes Carlstedt was a first-grade aviation physician and practicing doctor in Norrköping. He was born on January 22, 1906 in Loftahammar, Kalmar province, to the parish priest Carl August C. and Elin Ringberg. He got married in 1936 to the RK-nurse Gerda Hertzman. Carlstedt finished high school in Eksjö in 1925 and became a medical candidate in Stockholm in 1929. He received his medical license there in 1934. He worked as an assistant doctor at S:t Eriks hospital with medical department in 1935, understudy doctor at Södermani 1. sanatorium in 1936-1938, second and first understudy doctor at Eskilstuna hospital with medical department in 1938-1941, understudy doctor at Strömstad's hospital in 1941-1942, temporary medical officer at Finspångs and Vara districts and temporary city physician in Eksjö, first-grade aviation physician in 1943, and practicing doctor in Norrköping since 1943.
